{"name": "happymeter", "metadata": {"name": "happymeter", "version": "2.0.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Find out how happy you are", "upload_time": 1735836759}, "documentation": ["# happymeter :blush:\n\n[![Build](https://github.com/mixklim/happymeter/actions/workflows/build.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/mixklim/happymeter/actions/workflows/build.yml)\n[![Coverage Status](./reports/coverage/coverage-badge.svg?dummy=8484744)](./reports/coverage/index.html)\n\n##### Find out how happy you are\n\nML model based on [Somerville Happiness Survey Data Set](https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Somerville+Happiness+Survey#).\n\n##### To run locally (from root folder):\n\n- Create virtual environment: `python -m venv .venv`\n- Install dependencies: `poetry install --no-root`\n- Launch backend: `make backend`\n- Launch front-end:\n  - Native (HTML + CSS + JS): [127.0.0.1:8080](http://127.0.0.1:8080/)\n  - Streamlit: `make frontend`\n- Pre-commit: `make eval`\n- Unit tests: `make test`\n- Coverage badge: `make cov`\n- End-to-end build (eval + test + cov): `make build`\n\n##### Containers:\n\n- Populate `.env` with `POSTGRES_USER`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` and `POSTGRES_DB`\n- Docker backend: `make docker-backend`\n- Docker frontend: `make docker-frontend`\n- Docker compose: `make docker-compose`\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "app.model", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "app.model.SurveyMeasurement", "bases": ["BaseModel"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "app.model.SurveyMeasurement.city_services", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "app.m